Welcoming the delivery of the new skip bins are Social Services Portfolio Councillor Daniel Benson (centre), Environmental Health Manager Nomvula Machelesi and Acting Cleansing and Parks Manager Frank Tamboer. Photo:SUPPLIED Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories KOUGA Municipality has increased its efforts to fight illegal dumping and keep communities clean by acquiring 20 new skip bins. The 6m² containers, worth R348 840 in total, have been distributed to hot spots for illegal dumping. Executive Mayor Elza van Lingen said the municipality was intensifying its war against waste to ensure that all of Kouga’s people live, work and play in clean and healthy environments. She asked communities to please take note of the following: 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  